Add dashboard build pipeline (esbuild) + dashboard/src tree

First stage of the "real build + split into modules" item: introduce the
build, defer the per-feature module split (next push).

- dashboard/src/: index.html template (with /*__CSS__*/ + /*__JS__*/
  placeholders), styles.css, main.js (the JS, IIFE wrapper dropped — esbuild
  provides scope).
- dashboard/build.mjs: esbuild bundles main.js -> single IIFE, inlined with
  styles.css into one self-contained dist/index.html. Guards that the
  __BOOKCLAW_AUTH_TOKEN__ placeholder survives into the output. --watch mode.
- package.json: build:dashboard / build:dashboard:watch; esbuild added as an
  explicit devDependency (was transitive via tsx); lockfile synced.
- docker/Dockerfile: builder copies dashboard/ and runs the build before the
  dev-dep prune; runtime copies the freshly-built dashboard from the builder
  (never ships a stale committed dist).
- dist/index.html stays committed (source of truth is src/) so local start +
  smoke/API tests need no build step. CLAUDE.md: edit src/, not dist/.

Behavior-preserving: served HTML is equivalent to the old monolith (esbuild
strips comments, so it's smaller). Per-feature split of main.js into
lib/+panels/ tracked as a follow-up TODO (shared-state object refactor, done
incrementally with Mercury visual checks — no behavioral test net).

Verified: build clean (placeholder + key fns present); npm test green
(29 unit + API + smoke, incl. dashboard-serves-with-token).
